        Title Insurance in Brisbane: What It Covers and Whether You Need It
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:rgba(240,236,228,0.6);line-height:1.8;max-width:54ch;">
        Title insurance is a one-off policy that protects buyers (and sometimes sellers) against hidden title defects, fraud, unregistered easements, and survey errors. Here is what it covers, what it does not, and when it is worth the premium in Queensland.
      </p>
